READ ME FOR INSTALLING POSTGRES(DB)

Go online and download and install PgAdmin4

We will use Docker, a package (image) manager that provides the same envioroment for everyone. No matter OS, versions, etc. 

Go to 
https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/

Run 
$ sudo apt-get update

$ sudo apt-get install \
    apt-transport-https \
    ca-certificates \
    curl \
    gnupg-agent \
    software-properties-common

$ curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo apt-key add -

$ sudo apt-key fingerprint 0EBFCD88

$ pub   rsa4096 2017-02-22 [SCEA]

$ 9DC8 5822 9FC7 DD38 854A  E2D8 8D81 803C 0EBF CD88

$ sudo add-apt-repository \
>    "deb [arch=amd64] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
>    $(lsb_release -cs) \
>    stable"

$ sudo apt-get update

$ sudo apt-get install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io

$ sudo docker run hello-world

$ sudo docker pull postgres

$ mkdir -p $HOME/docker/volumes/postgres

$ sudo docker run --rm   --name pg-docker -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=docker -d -p 5432:5432 -v $HOME/docker/volumes/postgres:/var/lib/postgresql/data  postgres

$ sudo docker ps

FROM THIS POINT WE CAN OPEN OUR INTERFACE PGADMIN4 and login with 
user: pg-docker
psd: docker
port: 0.0.0.0 (external connection)
      5432 (internal) 

